something. Form over function.

00:27:45.360 --> 00:27:47.750
Like

00:27:47.760 --> 00:27:49.590
object-oriented and functional both give

00:27:49.600 --> 00:27:52.310
you a very dogmatic, prescriptive way to

00:27:52.320 --> 00:27:54.389
do everything.

00:27:54.399 --> 00:27:56.389
There are occasions when either of those

00:27:56.399 --> 00:27:58.470
approaches are better suited to a very

00:27:58.480 --> 00:28:01.750
specific problem. However, in practice,

00:28:01.760 --> 00:28:04.630
they're both very, very heavy ways to

00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:07.110
program that change how you would have

00:28:07.120 --> 00:28:09.350
to write things from the normal just do

00:28:09.360 --> 00:28:11.510
it in the shortest way possible. They

00:28:11.520 --> 00:28:14.470
change a lot um from what you would do

00:28:14.480 --> 00:28:15.750
without having either of those

00:28:15.760 --> 00:28:17.510
preconceptions.

00:28:17.520 --> 00:28:21.590
And it is very very rare that a specific

00:28:21.600 --> 00:28:24.870
topic justifies that big of a change in

00:28:24.880 --> 00:28:35.750
how you would approach the problem.

00:28:37.430 --> 00:28:37.440
The problem is that if you're introduced

00:28:37.440 --> 00:28:39.750
to object-oriented or functional very

00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:42.470
early on, they will like whatever you're

